class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}
```

In this code, we first initialize an array degree of size n to record the in-degree of each team. Then we iterate over the edges, for each edge, we increment the in-degree of the destination team.

After that, we iterate over the teams, if a team has an in-degree of 0, we consider it as a potential champion. If we find a team with an in-degree of 0 and we haven't found a champion yet, we set this team as the champion. If we find another team with an in-degree of 0 and we have already found a champion, we return -1 because there are more than one teams with an in-degree of 0, which means there are multiple champions.

Finally, we return the champion. If we can't find a champion, we return -1.

