class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0; // 操作次数
            int and = -1; // -1 的二进制全为 1
            for (int x : nums) {
                and &= x & mask;
                if (and != 0) {
                    cnt++; // 合并 x，操作次数加一
                } else {
                    and = -1; // 准备合并下一段
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= mask; // 答案的这个比特位必须是 1
                mask ^= 1 << b; // 后面不考虑这个比特位
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```
In the given code, the logic behind it is to calculate the minimum possible value of the bitwise OR of the remaining elements of nums after applying at most k operations. This is done by iterating over each bit of the maximum number and counting the number of times we can merge the numbers with the given bit. If the count is greater than k, it means we cannot merge all the numbers with the given bit, so we set the bit in the answer. If not, we exclude the bit from the mask and move on to the next bit.

