class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```

This code works by iterating over the array and checking each number's number of set bits. If the number of set bits is the same as the previous number, the current number is added to the current group's maximum. If the number of set bits is different, the previous group's maximum is updated and the current number becomes the start of a new group.

If any number is less than the previous group's maximum, the array cannot be sorted because the numbers in the same group must be in non-decreasing order. If no such number is found, the array can be sorted, so the function returns true.

