class Solution {
public:
    int minimizeMax(vector<int> &nums, int p) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int left = -1, right = nums.back() - nums[0] + 1; // 开区间
        while (left + 1 < right) { // 开区间
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            int cnt = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < nums.size() - 1; ++i)
                if (nums[i + 1] - nums[i] <= mid) { // 都选
                    ++cnt;
                    ++i;
                }
            if (cnt >= p)
                right = mid;
            else
                left = mid;
        }
        return right;
    }
};

This code first sorts the input array, then uses binary search to find the minimum maximum difference among all p pairs. The binary search range is [left, right), where left is -1 and right is nums.back() - nums[0] + 1 (the maximum possible difference + 1). The mid value is calculated as the average of left and right. The code then counts the number of pairs that have a difference less than or equal to mid. If the count is greater than or equal to p, then right is set to mid, otherwise left is set to mid. The binary search continues until the range is narrowed down to a single value, which is the minimum maximum difference.

